      "rationale": "Experimental validation tests conducted under ISO 14243-1 standardized loading conditions. Boundary conditions in FEA replicate the test rig constraints documented in the test protocol. Temperature, specimen preparation, and preconditioning protocols documented and matched between simulation and experiment. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-output-comparison-criteria",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison metrics include mean absolute percent error (MAPE), 95% prediction interval coverage, and Bland-Altman analysis for strain gauge validation (vr001) and mechanical test validation (vr002). MAPE 6.8% for surface strains; stiffness within 9%. All comparisons documented with uncertainty bounds from experimental measurement uncertainty. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-qoi-relevance-criteria",
      "rationale": "The primary QOI (peak von Mises stress in the tibial tray-stem junction) is directly validated through strain gauge measurements at locations identified via preliminary FEA stress mapping. Secondary QOIs (global stiffness, yield load) validated against mechanical test data. QOI selection documented with traceability to clinical failure modes (fatigue cracking at tray-stem junction). Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-validation-relevance-criteria",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments use the same tibial tray geometry, material batch, and assembly configuration as the COU device. Loading conditions span the five physiological scenarios defined in the COU. Similarity assessment documented: geometry fidelity high, material fidelity high, loading fidelity moderate (simplified gait cycle representation). Residual extrapolation uncertainty quantified. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-solver-error-criteria",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence verified: energy norm residual < 1×10⁻⁶ for all load steps. Contact convergence monitored via force residual and penetration tolerance. Nonlinear solution stability confirmed across all five loading scenarios with no divergence events. Abaqus solver documentation confirms double-precision arithmetic throughout. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-use-error-criteria",
      "rationale": "Model use procedures documented in a controlled simulation plan reviewed by a second qualified analyst. Input deck peer review completed with documented sign-off. Boundary condition application verified against test rig drawings by independent reviewer. Analyst qualifications documented (10+ years FEA experience, ASME V&V 40 training completed). Achieved level 2 exceeds required level 1 for MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-model-form-criteria",
      "rationale": "Model form selection justified: linear elastic constitutive model for CoCr alloy and cortical bone (strains < 0.5% in all scenarios); elastic-perfectly-plastic model for UHMWPE insert. Justification documented with reference to published material characterization data. Viscoelastic bone remodeling excluded with documented rationale (acute loading scenarios only). Sensitivity of peak stress QOI to model form assumptions quantified via comparison with hyperelastic UHMWPE model (< 4% difference). Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-model-inputs-criteria",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from peer-reviewed literature and manufacturer data sheets with full traceability (dataset ds003). Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of production tibial tray (dataset ds004). Loading inputs derived from ISO 14243-1 and published gait analysis data. Sensitivity analysis (ValidationResult vr004) quantifies input uncertainty propagation; dominant input (cortical bone modulus) identified with Sobol index 0.61. Uncertainty bounds propagated to QOI predictions. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
